{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When I was seven years old\nand my sister was just five years old,"},{"time":3574,"text":"we were playing on top of a bunk bed."},{"time":6000,"text":"I was two years older\nthan my sister at the time --"},{"time":9050,"text":"I mean, I'm two years\nolder than her now --"},{"time":11306,"text":"but at the time it meant she had to do\neverything that I wanted to do,"},{"time":14655,"text":"and I wanted to play war."},{"time":16000,"text":"So we were up on top of our bunk beds."},{"time":18080,"text":"And on one side of the bunk bed,"},{"time":20199,"text":"I had put out all of my G.I. Joe\nsoldiers and weaponry."},{"time":22833,"text":"And on the other side were\nall my sister's My Little Ponies"},{"time":25745,"text":"ready for a cavalry charge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27214,"text":"There are differing accounts\nof what actually happened that afternoon,"},{"time":30531,"text":"but since my sister is not\nhere with us today,"},{"time":32843,"text":"let me tell you the true story --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34763,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"which is my sister's a little\non the clumsy side."},{"time":38459,"text":"Somehow, without any help or push\nfrom her older brother at all,"},{"time":41505,"text":"Amy disappeared\noff of the top of the bunk bed"},{"time":43999,"text":"and landed with this crash on the floor."},{"time":45953,"text":"I nervously peered\nover the side of the bed"},{"time":47991,"text":"to see what had befallen my fallen sister"},{"time":50000,"text":"and saw that she had landed\npainfully on her hands and knees"},{"time":52878,"text":"on all fours on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54253,"text":"I was nervous because\nmy parents had charged me"},{"time":56753,"text":"with making sure that my sister and I"},{"time":58639,"text":"played as safely\nand as quietly as possible."},{"time":61000,"text":"And seeing as how I had\naccidentally broken Amy's arm"},{"time":64676,"text":"just one week before --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70099,"text":"(Laughter ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":71124,"text":"heroically pushing her out of the way\nof an oncoming imaginary sniper bullet,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":75808,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":77866,"text":"for which I have yet to be thanked,\nI was trying as hard as I could --"},{"time":81973,"text":"she didn't even see it coming --"},{"time":83593,"text":"I was trying hard\nto be on my best behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85958,"text":"And I saw my sister's face,"},{"time":87332,"text":"this wail of pain\nand suffering and surprise"},{"time":89592,"text":"threatening to erupt from her mouth\nand wake my parents"},{"time":92300,"text":"from the long winter's nap\nfor which they had settled."},{"time":94920,"text":"So I did the only thing"},{"time":96100,"text":"my frantic seven year-old brain\ncould think to do to avert this tragedy."},{"time":99562,"text":"And if you have children,\nyou've seen this hundreds of times."},{"time":102449,"text":"I said, \"Amy, wait. Don't cry.\nDid you see how you landed?"},{"time":105200,"text":"No human lands on all fours like that."},{"time":108591,"text":"Amy, I think this means you're a unicorn.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114393,"text":"Now, that was cheating,"},{"time":115526,"text":"because there was nothing\nshe would want more"},{"time":117679,"text":"than not to be Amy\nthe hurt five year-old little sister,"},{"time":120344,"text":"but Amy the special unicorn."},{"time":121800,"text":"Of course, this option\nwas open to her brain"},{"time":123948,"text":"at no point in the past."},{"time":125156,"text":"And you could see how my poor,\nmanipulated sister faced conflict,"},{"time":128277,"text":"as her little brain attempted\nto devote resources"},{"time":130678,"text":"to feeling the pain and suffering\nand surprise she just experienced,"},{"time":134001,"text":"or contemplating her new-found\nidentity as a unicorn."},{"time":136570,"text":"And the latter won."},{"time":137700,"text":"Instead of crying or ceasing our play,"},{"time":139563,"text":"instead of waking my parents,"},{"time":141000,"text":"with all the negative consequences for me,"},{"time":143331,"text":"a smile spread across her face"},{"time":145000,"text":"and she scrambled back up\nonto the bunk bed"},{"time":147116,"text":"with all the grace of a baby unicorn --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149026,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151579,"text":"with one broken leg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152993,"text":"What we stumbled across"},{"time":154619,"text":"at this tender age\nof just five and seven --"},{"time":156723,"text":"we had no idea at the time --"},{"time":158419,"text":"was was going be at the vanguard\nof a scientific revolution"},{"time":161544,"text":"occurring two decades later in the way\nthat we look at the human brain."},{"time":165022,"text":"We had stumbled across\nsomething called positive psychology,"},{"time":167961,"text":"which is the reason I'm here today"},{"time":169630,"text":"and the reason that I wake up\nevery morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171742,"text":"When I started talking about this research"},{"time":173800,"text":"outside of academia,\nwith companies and schools,"},{"time":176100,"text":"the first thing they said to never do\nis to start with a graph."},{"time":179200,"text":"The first thing I want to do\nis start with a graph."},{"time":181678,"text":"This graph looks boring,"},{"time":183000,"text":"but it is the reason I get excited\nand wake up every morning."},{"time":185975,"text":"And this graph doesn't even mean\nanything; it's fake data."},{"time":188764,"text":"What we found is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":190059,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"If I got this data studying you,\nI would be thrilled,"},{"time":196000,"text":"because there's a trend there,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and that means that I can get published,"},{"time":200000,"text":"which is all that really matters."},{"time":202000,"text":"There is one weird red dot\nabove the curve,"},{"time":204100,"text":"there's one weirdo in the room --"},{"time":206625,"text":"I know who you are, I saw you earlier --"},{"time":209674,"text":"that's no problem."},{"time":211000,"text":"That's no problem, as most of you know,\nbecause I can just delete that dot."},{"time":215000,"text":"I can delete that dot because\nthat's clearly a measurement error."},{"time":218128,"text":"And we know that's a measurement error\nbecause it's messing up my data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221518,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222581,"text":"So one of the first things we teach people"},{"time":224768,"text":"in economics, statistics,\nbusiness and psychology courses"},{"time":227608,"text":"is how, in a statistically valid way,\ndo we eliminate the weirdos."},{"time":230797,"text":"How do we eliminate the outliers\nso we can find the line of best fit?"},{"time":234200,"text":"Which is fantastic\nif I'm trying to find out"},{"time":236320,"text":"how many Advil the average\nperson should be taking -- two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239100,"text":"But if I'm interested in your potential,"},{"time":241935,"text":"or for happiness or productivity\nor energy or creativity,"},{"time":245000,"text":"we're creating the cult\nof the average with science."},{"time":247595,"text":"If I asked a question like,"},{"time":249000,"text":"\"How fast can a child learn\nhow to read in a classroom?\""},{"time":251721,"text":"scientists change the answer to"},{"time":253230,"text":"\"How fast does the average child\nlearn how to read in that classroom?\""},{"time":256593,"text":"and we tailor the class\ntowards the average."},{"time":258763,"text":"If you fall below the average,"},{"time":260310,"text":"then psychologists get thrilled,"},{"time":261927,"text":"because that means you're\ndepressed or have a disorder,"},{"time":264767,"text":"or hopefully both."},{"time":266000,"text":"We're hoping for both\nbecause our business model is,"},{"time":268500,"text":"if you come into a therapy\nsession with one problem,"},{"time":271000,"text":"we want to make sure you\nleave knowing you have ten,"},{"time":273500,"text":"so you keep coming back."},{"time":274700,"text":"We'll go back into your\nchildhood if necessary,"},{"time":276939,"text":"but eventually we want\nto make you normal again."},{"time":279239,"text":"But normal is merely average."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280700,"text":"And positive psychology posits\nthat if we study what is merely average,"},{"time":284072,"text":"we will remain merely average."},{"time":286428,"text":"Then instead of deleting\nthose positive outliers,"},{"time":288746,"text":"what I intentionally do is come\ninto a population like this one"},{"time":291812,"text":"and say, why?"},{"time":292852,"text":"Why are some of you high above the curve"},{"time":294800,"text":"in terms of intellectual,\nathletic, musical ability,"},{"time":297409,"text":"creativity, energy levels,"},{"time":298700,"text":"resiliency in the face\nof challenge, sense of humor?"},{"time":301200,"text":"Whatever it is, instead of deleting\nyou, what I want to do is study you."},{"time":304767,"text":"Because maybe we can glean information,"},{"time":306700,"text":"not just how to move\npeople up to the average,"},{"time":308878,"text":"but move the entire average up\nin our companies and schools worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312300,"text":"The reason this graph is important to me"},{"time":314300,"text":"is, on the news, the majority\nof the information is not positive."},{"time":317400,"text":"in fact it's negative."},{"time":318500,"text":"Most of it's about murder, corruption,\ndiseases, natural disasters."},{"time":321700,"text":"And very quickly, my brain starts to think"},{"time":323800,"text":"that's the accurate ratio\nof negative to positive in the world."},{"time":326819,"text":"This creates\n\"the medical school syndrome.\""},{"time":329047,"text":"During the first year of medical training,"},{"time":331627,"text":"as you read through a list of all\nthe symptoms and diseases,"},{"time":335039,"text":"suddenly you realize you have all of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337294,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338319,"text":"I have a brother in-law named Bobo,\nwhich is a whole other story."},{"time":341415,"text":"Bobo married Amy the unicorn."},{"time":343001,"text":"Bobo called me on the phone --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344757,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346926,"text":"from Yale Medical School,"},{"time":349000,"text":"and Bobo said, \"Shawn, I have leprosy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":351305,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"Which, even at Yale,\nis extraordinarily rare."},{"time":355611,"text":"But I had no idea how to console poor Bobo"},{"time":358000,"text":"because he had just gotten\nover an entire week of menopause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360882,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"We're finding it's not necessarily\nthe reality that shapes us,"},{"time":365000,"text":"but the lens through which your brain\nviews the world that shapes your reality."},{"time":368800,"text":"And if we can change the lens,\nnot only can we change your happiness,"},{"time":372101,"text":"we can change every single educational\nand business outcome at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375773,"text":"I applied to Harvard on a dare."},{"time":377300,"text":"I didn't expect to get in, and my family\nhad no money for college."},{"time":380500,"text":"When I got a military scholarship\ntwo weeks later, they let me go."},{"time":383700,"text":"Something that wasn't\neven a possibility became a reality."},{"time":386500,"text":"I assumed everyone there\nwould see it as a privilege as well,"},{"time":389500,"text":"that they'd be excited to be there."},{"time":391200,"text":"Even in a classroom\nfull of people smarter than you,"},{"time":393700,"text":"I felt you'd be happy just to be\nin that classroom."},{"time":396200,"text":"But what I found is,\nwhile some people experience that,"},{"time":398900,"text":"when I graduated after my four years"},{"time":400700,"text":"and then spent the next eight years\nliving in the dorms with the students --"},{"time":404301,"text":"Harvard asked me to; I wasn't that guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406204,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"I was an officer to counsel students\nthrough the difficult four years."},{"time":411400,"text":"And in my research and my teaching,"},{"time":413191,"text":"I found that these students,\nno matter how happy they were"},{"time":415991,"text":"with their original success\nof getting into the school,"},{"time":418700,"text":"two weeks later their brains were focused,\nnot on the privilege of being there,"},{"time":422500,"text":"nor on their philosophy or physics,"},{"time":424200,"text":"but on the competition, the workload,"},{"time":426000,"text":"the hassles, stresses, complaints."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427700,"text":"When I first went in there, I walked\ninto the freshmen dining hall,"},{"time":430900,"text":"which is where my friends from Waco,\nTexas, which is where I grew up --"},{"time":434300,"text":"I know some of you know this."},{"time":435800,"text":"When they'd visit, they'd look around,"},{"time":437700,"text":"and say, \"This dining hall looks like\nsomething out of Hogwart's.\""},{"time":440900,"text":"It does, because that was Hogwart's\nand that's Harvard."},{"time":443500,"text":"And when they see this,"},{"time":444700,"text":"they say, \"Why do you waste your time\nstudying happiness at Harvard?"},{"time":448000,"text":"What does a Harvard student\npossibly have to be unhappy about?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":451100,"text":"Embedded within that question"},{"time":452600,"text":"is the key to understanding\nthe science of happiness."},{"time":455200,"text":"Because what that question assumes"},{"time":456900,"text":"is that our external world\nis predictive of our happiness levels,"},{"time":459996,"text":"when in reality, if I know everything\nabout your external world,"},{"time":463096,"text":"I can only predict 10%\nof your long-term happiness."},{"time":465600,"text":"90 percent of your long-term happiness\nis predicted not by the external world,"},{"time":469400,"text":"but by the way your brain\nprocesses the world."},{"time":471615,"text":"And if we change it,"},{"time":472700,"text":"if we change our formula\nfor happiness and success,"},{"time":475153,"text":"we can change the way\nthat we can then affect reality."},{"time":477999,"text":"What we found is that only 25%\nof job successes are predicted by IQ,"},{"time":482000,"text":"75 percent of job successes"},{"time":484000,"text":"are predicted by your optimism\nlevels, your social support"},{"time":487000,"text":"and your ability to see stress\nas a challenge instead of as a threat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490300,"text":"I talked to a New England boarding school,\nprobably the most prestigious one,"},{"time":494000,"text":"and they said, \"We already know that."},{"time":495800,"text":"So every year, instead of just teaching\nour students, we have a wellness week."},{"time":499500,"text":"And we're so excited. Monday night\nwe have the world's leading expert"},{"time":502800,"text":"will speak about adolescent depression."},{"time":504700,"text":"Tuesday night\nit's school violence and bullying."},{"time":506963,"text":"Wednesday night is eating disorders."},{"time":508800,"text":"Thursday night is illicit drug use."},{"time":510500,"text":"And Friday night we're trying to decide\nbetween risky sex or happiness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":513953,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"I said, \"That's most people's\nFriday nights.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":517167,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Which I'm glad you liked,\nbut they did not like that at all."},{"time":525882,"text":"Silence on the phone."},{"time":527000,"text":"And into the silence, I said,\n\"I'd be happy to speak at your school,"},{"time":530300,"text":"but that's not a wellness week,\nthat's a sickness week."},{"time":533000,"text":"You've outlined all the negative\nthings that can happen,"},{"time":535700,"text":"but not talked about the positive.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":537400,"text":"The absence of disease is not health."},{"time":539200,"text":"Here's how we get to health:"},{"time":540600,"text":"We need to reverse the formula\nfor happiness and success."},{"time":543400,"text":"In the last three years,\nI've traveled to 45 countries,"},{"time":546100,"text":"working with schools and companies\nin the midst of an economic downturn."},{"time":549600,"text":"And I found that\nmost companies and schools"},{"time":551700,"text":"follow a formula\nfor success, which is this:"},{"time":553796,"text":"If I work harder, I'll be more successful."},{"time":555896,"text":"And if I'm more successful,\nthen I'll be happier."},{"time":558300,"text":"That undergirds most\nof our parenting and managing styles,"},{"time":561100,"text":"the way that we motivate our behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"And the problem is it's scientifically\nbroken and backwards for two reasons."},{"time":566644,"text":"Every time your brain has a success,"},{"time":568400,"text":"you just changed the goalpost\nof what success looked like."},{"time":571200,"text":"You got good grades,\nnow you have to get better grades,"},{"time":573901,"text":"you got into a good school\nand after you get into a better one,"},{"time":576896,"text":"you got a good job,\nnow you have to get a better job,"},{"time":579497,"text":"you hit your sales target,\nwe're going to change it."},{"time":581998,"text":"And if happiness is on the opposite side\nof success, your brain never gets there."},{"time":585899,"text":"We've pushed happiness\nover the cognitive horizon, as a society."},{"time":589000,"text":"And that's because we think\nwe have to be successful,"},{"time":591548,"text":"then we'll be happier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592696,"text":"But our brains work in the opposite order."},{"time":594795,"text":"If you can raise somebody's level\nof positivity in the present,"},{"time":597796,"text":"then their brain experiences what we now\ncall a happiness advantage,"},{"time":601060,"text":"which is your brain at positive\nperforms significantly better"},{"time":603998,"text":"than at negative, neutral or stressed."},{"time":605890,"text":"Your intelligence rises, your creativity\nrises, your energy levels rise."},{"time":609344,"text":"In fact, we've found that every single\nbusiness outcome improves."},{"time":612539,"text":"Your brain at positive\nis 31% more productive"},{"time":614692,"text":"than your brain at negative,\nneutral or stressed."},{"time":617026,"text":"You're 37% better at sales."},{"time":618426,"text":"Doctors are 19 percent\nfaster, more accurate"},{"time":620546,"text":"at coming up with the correct diagnosis"},{"time":622500,"text":"when positive instead\nof negative, neutral or stressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625200,"text":"Which means we can reverse the formula."},{"time":627100,"text":"If we can find a way of becoming\npositive in the present,"},{"time":629900,"text":"then our brains work\neven more successfully"},{"time":631972,"text":"as we're able to work harder,\nfaster and more intelligently."},{"time":634900,"text":"We need to be able to reverse this formula"},{"time":637000,"text":"so we can start to see what our brains\nare actually capable of."},{"time":640000,"text":"Because dopamine, which floods\ninto your system when you're positive,"},{"time":643300,"text":"has two functions."},{"time":644388,"text":"Not only does it make you happier,"},{"time":646389,"text":"it turns on all of the learning\ncenters in your brain"},{"time":648990,"text":"allowing you to adapt\nto the world in a different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651591,"text":"We've found there are ways\nthat you can train your brain"},{"time":654292,"text":"to be able to become more positive."},{"time":655993,"text":"In just a two-minute span of time\ndone for 21 days in a row,"},{"time":658987,"text":"we can actually rewire your brain,"},{"time":660688,"text":"allowing your brain to actually work\nmore optimistically and more successfully."},{"time":664589,"text":"We've done these things in research now"},{"time":666490,"text":"in every company that I've worked with,"},{"time":668491,"text":"getting them to write down three new\nthings that they're grateful for"},{"time":671792,"text":"for 21 days in a row,\nthree new things each day."},{"time":674103,"text":"And at the end of that,"},{"time":675294,"text":"their brain starts to retain a pattern"},{"time":677195,"text":"of scanning the world not for\nthe negative, but for the positive first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680696,"text":"Journaling about one positive experience\nyou've had over the past 24 hours"},{"time":684297,"text":"allows your brain to relive it."},{"time":685880,"text":"Exercise teaches your brain\nthat your behavior matters."},{"time":688561,"text":"We find that meditation allows your brain"},{"time":690562,"text":"to get over the cultural ADHD\nthat we've been creating"},{"time":693163,"text":"by trying to do multiple tasks at once"},{"time":695064,"text":"and allows our brains\nto focus on the task at hand."},{"time":697565,"text":"And finally, random acts of kindness\nare conscious acts of kindness."},{"time":700866,"text":"We get people,\nwhen they open up their inbox,"},{"time":703034,"text":"to write one positive email"},{"time":704368,"text":"praising or thanking somebody\nin their support network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707069,"text":"And by doing these activities"},{"time":708570,"text":"and by training your brain\njust like we train our bodies,"},{"time":711271,"text":"what we've found is we can reverse\nthe formula for happiness and success,"},{"time":714772,"text":"and in doing so, not only create\nripples of positivity,"},{"time":717499,"text":"but a real revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718600,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719700,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}